.SH NAME
closedir \- close a gangbangin' finger-lickin' directory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <sys/types.h>
.sp
.B #include <dirent.h>
.sp
.BI "int closedir(DIR *" dirp );
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR closedir ()
function closes tha directory stream associated with
.IR dirp .
A successful call to
.BR closedir ()
also closes tha underlyin file descriptor associated with
.IR dirp .
Da directory stream descriptor
.I dirp
is not available
afta dis call.
.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.BR closedir ()
function returns 0 on success.
On error, \-1 is returned, and
.I errno
is set appropriately.
.SH ERRORS
.TP
.B EBADF
Invalid directory stream descriptor
.IR dirp .
